<http://identifiers.org/uniprot/Q9H0P0-4>
        a       owl:Class .

:R-HSA-73621  a             owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0046135 ;
        rdfs:comment        "In parallel sequences of three reactions each, thymine is converted to beta-aminoisobutyrate and uracil is converted to beta-alanine. Both of these molecules are excreted in human urine and appear to be normal end products of pyrimidine catabolism (Griffith 1986; Webster et al. 2001). Mitochondrial AGXT2, however, can also catalyze the transamination of both molecules with pyruvate, yielding 2-oxoacids that can be metabolized further by reactions of branched-chain amino acid and short-chain fatty acid catabolism (Tamaki et al. 2000). The importance of these reactions in normal human pyrimidine catabolism has not been well worked out." ;
        rdfs:label          "Pyrimidine catabolism" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Jassal, B, 2003-06-17 09:00:26" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-73621" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-8956319/R-HSA-8956319> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

